==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English. From Old French, ''en gogues'', in a merry mood. See also the Italian ''agogare'', to desire eagerly.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-agog.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒɡ|-ɒɡ]]

===Adverb===
'''agog'''
# In a state of high anticipation or interest.
# Highly excited. Anxious, eager, impatient.

